markdown: <::EFFECT OF DIET ON FOOD CONSUMED IN COLD- AND WARM- ACCLIMATIZED RATS : chart Y-axis: MEAN GRAMS FOOD CONSUMED DAILY, ranging from 12 to 19 X-axis: PERCENT PROTEIN IN DIET, with major ticks at 7.5, 20, and 40 Legend: Fructose: - Dashed line with open circles, labeled 4°C, showing values: (7.5, 18.7), (20, 18.2), (40, 17.2) - Dashed line with open circles, labeled 24°C, showing values: (7.5, 14.0), (20, 15.8), (40, 16.2) Glucose: - Solid line with filled circles, labeled 4°C, showing values: (7.5, 17.5), (20, 16.7), (40, 16.0) - Solid line with filled circles, labeled 24°C, showing values: (7.5, 15.0), (20, 15.1), (40, 15.7) ::> FIGURE 1 FOOD CONSUMED CALORIC EFFICIENCY = Mean Daily Body Weight Gain (Gm) / Mean Daily Food Consumption (Gm) 1 Gm of each diet = 4.366 Calories <::A line graph with 'CALORIC EFFICIENCY x 100' on the y-axis and 'PERCENT PROTEIN IN DIET' on the x-axis. The x-axis shows values 0, 7.5, 20, and 40. The y-axis shows values 0 through 9. There are two sets of data, one for 24°C and one for 4°C. For 24°C: * A solid line represents 'Glucose', with data points approximately at (7.5, 1.3), (20, 7.7), and (40, 8.5). * A dashed line represents 'Fructose', with data points approximately at (7.5, 2.8), (20, 7.5), and (40, 8.2). For 4°C: * A solid line represents 'Glucose', with data points approximately at (7.5, 1.3), (20, 1.8), and (40, 2.2). * A dashed line represents 'Fructose', with data points approximately at (7.5, 1.8), (20, 2.3), and (40, 2.4). : chart::> FIGURE 2 CALORIC EFFICIENCY -13- Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/slmg0227
